{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17652280","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17652280"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T21:34:39+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T21:34:39+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18529"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18529","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18529"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.08,0,0.08,0,0.83]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11261"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75806"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11261","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11261"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18529"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61319"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"31"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"78"},{"type":"tags","id":"414"},{"type":"tags","id":"937"},{"type":"tags","id":"3898"},{"type":"tags","id":"4945"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"5631"},{"type":"tags","id":"8088"},{"type":"tags","id":"10773"},{"type":"tags","id":"10794"},{"type":"tags","id":"11199"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"26112"},{"type":"contributions","id":"26115"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75806","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/75806"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 42-year-old woman undergoes genetic testing which identifies a pathogenic variant in the BRCA1 gene, associated with increased risk of breast and ovarian cancer. She has two sisters and a daughter, none of whom are aware of the testing.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the healthcare provider\u0027s primary ethical obligation regarding the genetic test result?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Directly contact all biological relatives","Share results with healthcare providers of the family members","Maintain absolute confidentiality without discussion","Request court order for disclosure","Inform the patient about implications for family members"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe correct approach is to \u003Cstrong\u003Einform the patient about implications for family members\u003C/strong\u003E. Healthcare providers should discuss how the genetic test results may impact biological relatives and encourage the patient to share this information with family members who could benefit from genetic counselling or testing.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDirectly contact all biological relatives\u003C/strong\u003E - This violates patient confidentiality and privacy laws\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMaintain absolute confidentiality without discussion\u003C/strong\u003E - This fails to address the preventive healthcare opportunities for at-risk relatives\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERequest court order for disclosure\u003C/strong\u003E - This is unnecessarily aggressive and legally complex when patient education is the appropriate first step\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EShare results with healthcare providers of the family members\u003C/strong\u003E - This does not address the core ethical obligation to inform the patient about familial implications.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe healthcare provider should support the patient in understanding the familial nature of genetic information and assist in developing strategies for communicating results to relatives, while respecting patient autonomy and confidentiality.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Genetic testing results have implications for biological relatives who may share disease-causing variants.","Healthcare providers have a duty to inform patients about familial implications of genetic test results.","Patient confidentiality must be balanced against potential benefits to relatives who could access preventive care."],"references":["Petrova D, Cruz M, S\u00e1nchez MJ. BRCA1/2 testing for genetic susceptibility to cancer after 25 years: A scoping review and a primer on ethical implications. Breast. 2022 Feb;61:66-76. Available at: https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC8686063/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61319"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18529"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61319","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/61319"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-31T15:21:56+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-31T15:21:57+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11261"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75806"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"25","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/25"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc68\u200d\ud83d\udc69\u200d\ud83d\udc66","name":"General Practice","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"6"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"31","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/31"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udf97","name":"Oncology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:45+10:30"},"relation